    <metadata>
        <name>Rosedale-Hartoft Bridge-Lastingham</name>
        <desc>Wet sections of path between Hartoft Bridge and Tranmire Beck can be easily avoided by walking locally through heather (easy). 

The wet patch with reeds below the spring east of Askew Rigg can be minimised by locally keeping 50m or so north of the line of the path.

Tranmire Beck no longer has a footbridge, but it can be forded, or alternatively the beck can be easily jumped (1m wide) about 20m downstream.</desc>
        <bounds minlat="54.3087700" minlon="-0.8955000" maxlat="54.3530000" maxlon="-0.8535600"/>
        <extensions>
            <os:version>2.0</os:version>
            <os:point lat="54.3530000" lon="-0.8871900" type="start"/>
            <os:point lat="54.3529900" lon="-0.8871700" type="end"/>
            <os:activity>ON_FOOT_WALKING</os:activity>
            <os:difficulty>EASY</os:difficulty>
            <os:paths/>
            <os:distance>12967.3324000</os:distance>
            <os:elevation_ascent>330.7100000</os:elevation_ascent>
            <os:route_type>SINGLE</os:route_type>
        </extensions>
    </metadata>
